cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis of a large dataset of text. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper analyzes the social connections between users and proposes methods to infer emotion networks based on user activity. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper may discuss the software and tools used to collect and analyze the dataset. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possibility as the paper deals with social media data and emotions expressed by users. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) is a less likely possibility as the paper does not seem to focus on cybersecurity specifically, but may touch upon privacy and security concerns related to social media data.
